16:56.460 --> 16:59.340
If I didn't put that there, and it was just order.jsx,

16:59.340 --> 17:01.260
it would just load it immediately every single time.

17:01.260 --> 17:02.140
In our particular case,

17:02.140 --> 17:04.820
our components and our routes are fairly small.

17:04.820 --> 17:07.460
I probably wouldn't lazy load these.

17:07.460 --> 17:10.220
I probably would just load everything every single time.

17:10.220 --> 17:12.300
But if you're building an app of any size,

17:12.300 --> 17:14.080
these routes tend to get a little bit bigger

17:14.080 --> 17:15.820
every single time.

17:15.820 --> 17:17.660
So in that case, I probably would lazy load them,

17:17.660 --> 17:18.900
which is why I'm gonna show you today

17:18.900 --> 17:20.740
everything we're just gonna lazy load.

